This place has the best perigeos in all of New York City. They are hand made on site. My favorite are the sauerkraut and mushroom though the potato and cheese are a close runner up. The white borscht is also phenomenal! If you really want to treat yourself get the Polish platter with kielbasa, hot red sauerkraut, stuffed cabbage and your choice of Perigeos. Very friendly family place. Oh! The potato pancakes will also beat any others you have ever tried. Amazing place!

I usually don't write reviews but I feel like this place deserves one. I've ordered from here maybe 50 times over the course of 7 years. The food is ALWAYS good. It has never been cold, never an item forgotten, the entire menu is cooked well and quality control is on point. Their prices are reasonable + the owner can be seen there many nights and he obviously takes care to keep the quality of the food up to par. I can't recommend it enough. The potato pancakes, pierogis, stuffed cabbage and all their sides are especially good. I hope this place is around forever.

I was really disappointed with half of our order. However, sauerkraut and assorted pierogi were amazing. But I won’t eat here again. It was just a waste of money. Service wasn’t great either. Waitress was serving all tables before taking our order and before bringing us food out.
